===Etymology===
1619; alteration of earlier {{term|wolvering|lang=en}} (1574), diminutive of {{term|wolver|lang=en}} ‘ravenous or savage animal; person who behaves like a wolf’ (1593),<ref>Robert K. Barnhart, ed., ''Chambers Dictionary of Etymology'' (Edinburgh: Chambers, 2008), 1242.</ref> ultimately from {{term|wolf|lang=en}}.

